{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860744176,"sessionID":"ses_28673b592ffesLzPwf0zFlWb2V","part":{"id":"prt_d798c7fb2001kagLUcRoDwo5VG","messageID":"msg_d798c67b10016Kr1gECs92II3z","sessionID":"ses_28673b592ffesLzPwf0zFlWb2V","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-da09f18013ed487da112a996b698dad3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Add valkey-go dependency\n20:   - Run: `go get github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go@latest`\n21:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && cat go.mod | grep valkey-go`\n22:   - Independently verifiable: Dependency appears in go.mod\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Verify miniredis for testing\n25:   - Check: `cat go.mod | grep miniredis` (already present)\n26:   - Independently verifiable: Dependency confirmed\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ### Phase 2: Create valkeyStore Struct and Constructor\n31: \n32: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` with struct definition\n33:   - Define `valkeyStore struct` with `cli valkey.Client` field\n34:   - Add key constants: `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`\n35:   - Add `sessionKey(sessionID string) string` helper\n36:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n37:   - Independently verifiable: File compiles without error\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T2.2** Implement `newValkeyStore(opts *valkeyClientOption) (Store, error)`\n40:   - Use `valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{})`\n41:   - Set `InitAddress`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient`\n42:   - Return initialized `valkeyStore`\n43:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n44:   - Independently verifiable: Constructor compiles\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.3** Update `newValkeyStoreFromEnv()` in `store_redis.go`\n47:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated → split to InitAddress)\n48:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`\n49:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool)\n50:   - Call `newValkeyStore(opts)`\n51:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n52:   - Independently verifiable: Env parsing compiles\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Phase 3: Implement Store Interface Methods\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T3.1** Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error`\n59:   - Use `s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()`\n60:   - Check response == \"PONG\"\n61:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n62:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T3.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n65:   - Validate empty sessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n66:   - Use `s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n67:   - Detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp.Error())` → `ErrNotFound`\n68:   - JSON unmarshal → `types.SandboxInfo`\n69:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n70:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n73:   - Validate: nil sandbox, zero ExpiresAt, empty SessionID\n74:   - Use `DoMulti` for atomicity:\n75:     - `Setnx` for session key\n76:     - `Zadd` for expiryIndexKey\n77:     - `Zadd` for lastActivityIndexKey\n78:   - Check SETNX result → `ErrSessionExists` if not \"OK\"\n79:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n80:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n83:   - Validate: nil sandbox, empty SessionID\n84:   - Check existence via `Exists()` → `ErrNotFound`\n85:   - Use `Set()` to update JSON value\n86:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n87:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n88: \n89: - [ ] **T3.5** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error`\n90:   - Validate empty sessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n91:   - Use `DoMulti` for atomic cleanup:\n92:     - `Del` session key\n93:     - `Zrem` from expiryIndexKey\n94:     - `Zrem` from lastActivityIndexKey\n95:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n96:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.6** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n99:   - Return `nil` if limit <= 0\n100:   - Use `Zrangebyscore().Min(\"-inf\").Max(timestamp).Limit(0, limit)`\n101:   - Call `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` for batch retrieval\n102:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n103:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T3.7** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n106:   - Same pattern as T3.6 but uses `lastActivityIndexKey`\n107:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n108:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.8** Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n111:   - Build keys from sessionIDs\n112:   - Use `Mget()` for batch retrieval\n113:   - Skip missing keys (empty string)\n114:   - Skip unmarshal errors (continue)\n115:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n116:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T3.9** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n119:   - Validate empty sessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n120:   - Check existence → `ErrNotFound`\n121:   - Default `at` to `time.Now()` if zero\n122:   - Use `Zadd()` to update score in lastActivityIndexKey\n123:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n124:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T3.10** Implement `Close() error`\n127:   - Call `s.cli.Close()`\n128:   - Return nil\n129:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n130:   - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Phase 4: Remove Stub Implementation\n135: \n136: - [ ] **T4.1** Remove stub valkeyStore from `store_redis.go`\n137:   - Delete lines 384-439 (stub struct and methods)\n138:   - Keep `valkeyClientOption` struct and `newValkeyStoreFromEnv` logic\n139:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n140:   - Independently verifiable: Build succeeds\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: ### Phase 5: Unit Tests\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` with test helper\n147:   - Implement `setupTestValkeyStore(t) *valkeyStore`\n148:   - Use `miniredis.RunT(t)` as test server\n149:   - Create `valkey.NewClient()` connecting to miniredis\n150:   - Independently verifiable: Test helper compiles\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T5.2** Test `Ping` success\n153:   - Verify `Ping()` returns no error\n154:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T5.3** Test `GetSandboxBySessionID` scenarios\n157:   - Success: pre-populate key, verify retrieval\n158:   - NotFound: query missing key → `ErrNotFound`\n159:   - EmptySessionID: empty input → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n160:   - Independently verifiable: All 3 tests pass\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T5.4** Test `StoreSandbox` scenarios\n163:   - Success: verify key + both ZSET entries\n164:   - NilSandbox → `ErrNilSandbox`\n165:   - ZeroExpiresAt → `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n166:   - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n167:   - Duplicate → `ErrSessionExists`\n168:   - Independently verifiable: All 5 tests pass\n169: \n170: - [ ] **T5.5** Test `UpdateSandbox` scenarios\n171:   - Success: store first, update, verify new value\n172:   - NotFound → `ErrNotFound`\n173:   - NilSandbox → `ErrNilSandbox`\n174:   - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n175:   - Independently verifiable: All 4 tests pass\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T5.6** Test `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` scenarios\n178:   - Success: verify key + ZSETs removed\n179:   - NotFound: no error (idempotent)\n180:   - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n181:   - Independently verifiable: All 3 tests pass\n182: \n183: - [ ] **T5.7** Test `ListExpiredSandboxes` scenarios\n184:   - Success: expired vs active separation\n185:   - Limit: respect limit parameter\n186:   - ZeroLimit: return nil\n187:   - NegativeLimit: return nil\n188:   - SkipMissing: orphan ZSET entry skipped\n189:   - Empty: return nil when no expired\n190:   - Independently verifiable: All 6 tests pass\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T5.8** Test `ListInactiveSandboxes` scenarios\n193:   - Success: inactive vs active separation\n194:   - Limit: respect limit parameter\n195:   - ZeroLimit: return nil\n196:   - Empty: return nil when no inactive\n197:   - Independently verifiable: All 4 tests pass\n198: \n199: - [ ] **T5.9** Test `UpdateSessionLastActivity` scenarios\n200:   - Success: verify ZSET score updated\n201:   - ZeroTime: defaults to `time.Now()`\n202:   - NotFound → `ErrNotFound`\n203:   - EmptySessionID → `ErrEmptySessionID`\n204:   - Independently verifiable: All 4 tests pass\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T5.10** Test `Close` and `Mget` batch load\n207:   - Close: verify client closes without error\n208:   - Mget: batch load with missing keys skipped\n209:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n210: \n211: - [ ] **T5.11** Test `newValkeyStoreFromEnv` scenarios\n212:   - Missing ADDR → error\n213:   - Missing password (required) → `ErrPasswordRequired`\n214:   - Password not required → success\n215:   - DisableCache / ForceSingle parsed correctly\n216:   - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ### Phase 6: Validation and Integration\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T6.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/store/...`\n223:   - Verify: No warnings\n224:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n225: \n226: - [ ] **T6.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/store/...`\n227:   - Verify: No errors\n228:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n229: \n230: - [ ] **T6.3** Run all tests with race detector\n231:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -race -v`\n232:   - Independently verifiable: All tests pass\n233: \n234: - [ ] **T6.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n235:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/store/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n236:   - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n237:   - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n238: \n239: - [ ] **T6.5** Verify integration with `Storage()` singleton\n240:   - Set `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n241:   - Call `Storage()` → returns valkeyStore\n242:   - Verify Ping works\n243:   - Independently verifiable: Integration test passes\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## Acceptance Criteria\n248: \n249: - [ ] valkeyStore 完整实现 Store 接口 (all 10 methods)\n250: - [ ] 支持 5 个环境变量配置\n251: - [ ] ZSET 索引正确维护 (expiry + last_activity)\n252: - [ ] 错误处理完善 (6 种错误类型)\n253: - [ ] Pass `go vet`\n254: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n255: - [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n256: - [ ] Integration with Storage() singleton works\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ## File Changes Summary\n261: \n262: | File | Action | Lines Changed |\n263: |------|--------|---------------|\n264: | `go.mod` | Modify | +1 (valkey-go dependency) |\n265: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Create | ~200 lines |\n266: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Modify | -60 lines (stub removal) |\n267: | `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` | Create | ~150 lines |\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## Implementation Notes\n272: \n273: - valkey-go Builder pattern: `s.cli.B().Get().Key(k).Build()`\n274: - Atomic multi-command: `s.cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n275: - Nil detection: `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)`\n276: - Response types: `ToString()`, `AsBytes()`, `AsInt64()`, `AsStrSlice()`\n277: - miniredis compatible with Valkey protocol\n\n(End of file - total 277 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` 