{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860866095,"sessionID":"ses_28673b592ffesLzPwf0zFlWb2V","part":{"id":"prt_d798e5bd0001E3XdpqP637HYzW","messageID":"msg_d798cac12001SlT1q0hQugiNNC","sessionID":"ses_28673b592ffesLzPwf0zFlWb2V","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3ba0a236929641ecafae004d387a6058","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md","content":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Add gin dependency\n  - Run: `go get github.com/gin-gonic/gin@v1.10.0`\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy && cat go.mod | grep gin-gonic`\n  - Independently verifiable: `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` appears in go.mod\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Add jwt dependency\n  - Run: `go get github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5@v5.2.0`\n  - Verify: `go mod tidy && cat go.mod | grep golang-jwt`\n  - Independently verifiable: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` appears in go.mod\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Create package directories\n  - Run: `mkdir -p pkg/picod cmd/picod`\n  - Verify: `ls pkg/picod cmd/picod`\n  - Independently verifiable: Both directories exist\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2: Config Struct\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/picod/config.go` with Config struct\n  - Define `Config struct` with `Port int` and `Workspace string` fields\n  - Add doc comment describing PicoD configuration\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: File compiles without error\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3: Server Struct and Constructor\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/picod/server.go` with Server struct\n  - Define `Server struct` with fields:\n    - `config *Config`\n    - `engine *gin.Engine`\n    - `httpServer *http.Server`\n    - `authManager *AuthManager`\n    - `workspace string`\n    - `startTime time.Time`\n  - Add `readHeaderTimeout = 10 * time.Second` constant\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Struct compiles without AuthManager reference error\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Implement `NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error)`\n  - Initialize `engine` with `gin.New()`\n  - Set `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)`\n  - Apply `gin.Logger()` and `gin.Recovery()` middleware\n  - Resolve workspace: empty → `os.Getwd()`, relative → `filepath.Abs(workspace)`\n  - Initialize `authManager` via `NewAuthManager()`\n  - Set `startTime = time.Now()`\n  - Configure `http.Server` with Addr, Handler, ReadHeaderTimeout\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Constructor compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Implement `Run(ctx context.Context) error`\n  - Call `s.httpServer.ListenAndServe()`\n  - Log error via `klog.ErrorS(err, \"server error\")` on failure\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Method compiles\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Implement route registration in `NewServer`\n  - Register `/health` with `HealthCheckHandler` (no auth)\n  - Create `/api` group with `authManager.AuthMiddleware()`\n  - Register `/api/execute` POST → `ExecuteHandler`\n  - Register `/api/files` POST → `UploadFileHandler`\n  - Register `/api/files` GET → `ListFilesHandler`\n  - Register `/api/files/*path` GET → `DownloadFileHandler`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Route registration compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4: AuthManager and JWT Middleware\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Create `pkg/picod/auth.go` with AuthManager struct\n  - Define `AuthManager struct` with `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` and `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n  - Add constants: `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Struct and constants compile\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Implement `NewAuthManager() (*AuthManager, error)`\n  - Call `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`\n  - Set `publicKey` from loaded key\n  - Return error if env var missing\n  - Return error if PEM decode fails\n  - Return error if PKIX parse fails\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Constructor compiles\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Implement `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv() (*rsa.PublicKey, error)`\n  - Read `os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)`\n  - Decode PEM block via `pem.Decode([]byte(pemKey))`\n  - Verify PEM block type is `\"PUBLIC KEY\"` (PKIX format)\n  - Parse via `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)`\n  - Type-assert to `*rsa.PublicKey`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n\n- [ ] **T4.4** Implement `AuthMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc`\n  - Extract `Authorization` header via `c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n  - Return 401 with `\"missing authorization header\"` if header missing\n  - Strip `\"Bearer \"` prefix\n  - Return 401 with `\"invalid token format\"` if prefix missing\n  - Parse JWT with options: `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n  - Validate signing method: type-assert to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`, reject non-RSA\n  - Return 401 with `\"invalid signing method\"` for non-RSA\n  - Verify signature with public key\n  - Return 401 with `\"invalid signature\"` for invalid signature\n  - Return 401 with `\"token is expired\"` for expired token\n  - Apply `http.MaxBytesReader(w, r.Body, MaxBodySize)` on success\n  - Call `c.Next()` on success\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Middleware compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5: Path Sanitization\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` with sanitizePath function\n  - Signature: `func sanitizePath(workspace, requestedPath string) (string, error)`\n  - Resolve workspace symlinks: `filepath.EvalSymlinks(workspace)`\n  - Clean requested path: `filepath.Clean(requestedPath)`\n  - Strip leading `/`: `strings.TrimPrefix(cleaned, \"/\")`\n  - Join with workspace: `filepath.Join(resolvedWorkspace, cleaned)`\n  - Check traversal: `filepath.Rel(workspace, candidate)`, error if starts with `..`\n  - Re-validate existing paths after symlink resolution\n  - Return sanitized absolute path\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6: Execute Handler\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Create `pkg/picod/execute.go` with structs\n  - Define `ExecuteRequest struct`:\n    - `Command []string` with `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n    - `Timeout string` with `json:\"timeout\"`\n    - `WorkingDir string` with `json:\"working_dir\"`\n    - `Env map[string]string` with `json:\"env\"`\n  - Define `ExecuteResponse struct`:\n    - `Stdout string`, `Stderr string`, `ExitCode int`\n    - `Duration float64`, `StartTime time.Time`, `EndTime time.Time`\n  - Add constants: `TimeoutExitCode = 124`, `defaultTimeout = 60 * time.Second`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Structs and constants compile\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Implement `ExecuteHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n  - Bind `ExecuteRequest` via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n  - Return 400 for binding failure\n  - Validate `len(req.Command) > 0`, return 400 with `\"missing command\"`\n  - Parse timeout via `time.ParseDuration(req.Timeout)`, use default on error\n  - Create context with deadline: `context.WithTimeout(c.Request.Context(), timeout)`\n  - Build command: `exec.CommandContext(ctx, req.Command[0], req.Command[1:]...)`\n  - Sanitize working directory via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n  - Set `cmd.Dir` to sanitized path or workspace\n  - Augment env: `cmd.Env = os.Environ()` + `req.Env` entries\n  - Capture stdout/stderr via `bytes.Buffer`\n  - Execute with timing: `startTime`, `endTime`, `cmd.Run()`\n  - Handle timeout: `ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded` → exitCode 124, stderr \"command timed out\"\n  - Handle exit error: `exec.ExitError.ExitCode()`\n  - Return 200 with `ExecuteResponse`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 7: File Handlers\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Create `pkg/picod/files.go` with structs\n  - Define `FileInfo struct`: `Path`, `Size`, `Mode`, `Modified`\n  - Define `UploadFileRequest struct`: `Path`, `Content` (Base64), `Mode`\n  - Define `FileEntry struct`: `Name`, `Size`, `Modified`, `Mode`, `IsDir`\n  - Define `ListFilesResponse struct`: `Files []FileEntry`, `Path string`\n  - Add constants: `maxFileMode = 0777`, `defaultFileMode = 0644`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Structs and constants compile\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Implement `parseFileMode(modeStr string) (os.FileMode, error)`\n  - Return `defaultFileMode` for empty string\n  - Parse via `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)`\n  - Return `defaultFileMode` on parse error\n  - Return error `\"invalid file mode\"` if mode > `maxFileMode`\n  - Return `os.FileMode(mode)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Implement `UploadFileHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n  - Detect content type: `c.ContentType()`\n  - Multipart: extract `path` via `c.PostForm(\"path\")`, `file` via `c.FormFile(\"file\")`, `mode` via `c.PostForm(\"mode\")`\n  - Return 400 for missing path/file\n  - JSON: bind `UploadFileRequest`, decode Base64 via `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString`\n  - Return 400 for invalid Base64\n  - Sanitize path via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n  - Parse mode via `parseFileMode`, return 400 if > 0777\n  - Create parent dirs: `os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(sanitizedPath), 0755)`\n  - Write file: `os.WriteFile(sanitizedPath, content, mode)`\n  - Return 200 with `FileInfo`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Implement `ListFilesHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n  - Extract path: `c.Query(\"path\")`\n  - Return 400 with `\"missing path parameter\"` if empty\n  - Sanitize path via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n  - Read directory: `os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)`\n  - Return 500 with `\"failed to read directory\"` on error\n  - Build `FileEntry` for each entry, skip failed `Info()`\n  - Format mode: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%04o\", info.Mode().Perm())`\n  - Return 200 with `ListFilesResponse`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n- [ ] **T7.5** Implement `DownloadFileHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n  - Extract path: `c.Param(\"path\")`\n  - Strip leading `/`: `strings.TrimPrefix(path, \"/\")`\n  - Sanitize path via `sanitizePath`, return 400 on escape\n  - Check existence: `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)`\n  - Return 404 with `\"file not found\"` if not exists\n  - Return 400 with `\"path is not a file\"` if directory\n  - Detect Content-Type: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(sanitizedPath))`\n  - Set `Content-Disposition`: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n  - Stream file: `c.File(sanitizedPath)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 8: Health Handler\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/picod/health.go`\n  - Define constants: `version = \"0.0.1\"`, `service = \"PicoD\"`\n  - Implement `HealthCheckHandler(c *gin.Context)`\n  - Return 200 with JSON: `status=\"ok\"`, `service`, `version`, `uptime=time.Since(startTime).String()`\n  - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n\n---\n\n### Phase 9: Entry Point\n\n- [ ] **T9.1** Create `cmd/picod/main.go`\n  - Set klog stderr: `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")`\n  - Init klog flags: `klog.InitFlags(nil)`\n  - Define `-port` flag with default 8080\n  - Define `-workspace` flag with default empty\n  - Parse flags: `flag.Parse()`\n  - Create `Config` from flag values\n  - Call `NewServer(config)`, `klog.Fatalf` on error\n  - Call `server.Run(context.Background())`\n  - Log startup: `klog.InfoS(\"PicoD started\", \"port\", port, \"workspace\", workspace)`\n  - Verify: `go build ./cmd/picod/`\n  - Independently verifiable: Binary builds successfully\n\n---\n\n### Phase 10: Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] **T10.1** Create `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` with test helpers\n  - Implement `setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server`\n  - Create temp workspace via `t.TempDir()`\n  - Generate RSA key pair for test JWT signing\n  - Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var with PEM public key\n  - Create `Server` with test workspace\n  - Independently verifiable: Test helper compiles\n\n- [ ] **T10.2** Test `sanitizePath` scenarios\n  - Valid relative path: returns absolute path within workspace\n  - Absolute path: strips leading `/`, resolves within workspace\n  - Path traversal `../escape`: returns error\n  - Deep traversal `subdir/../../escape`: returns error\n  - Null byte: cleaned safely\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T10.3** Test `AuthMiddleware` scenarios\n  - Missing Authorization: HTTP 401, `\"missing authorization header\"`\n  - Invalid format: HTTP 401\n  - Expired token: HTTP 401, `\"token is expired\"`\n  - HS256 token: HTTP 401, `\"invalid signing method\"`\n  - Valid RS256 token: request proceeds\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T10.4** Test `ExecuteHandler` scenarios\n  - Valid command `echo hello`: stdout=\"hello\\n\", exit_code=0\n  - Empty command: HTTP 400\n  - Timeout exceeded: exit_code=124, stderr=\"command timed out\"\n  - Invalid timeout string: uses default 60s\n  - Working directory: stdout shows subdir path\n  - Path escape working_dir: HTTP 400\n  - Environment augmentation: stdout contains MY_VAR\n  - Exit code propagation: exit_code=42 for `exit 42`\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T10.5** Test `UploadFileHandler` scenarios\n  - Multipart upload: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n  - JSON Base64 upload: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n  - Invalid Base64: HTTP 400\n  - Path escape: HTTP 400\n  - Invalid mode: uses default 0644\n  - Mode > 0777: HTTP 400\n  - Parent directory creation: parents created with 0755\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T10.6** Test `ListFilesHandler` scenarios\n  - Valid directory: HTTP 200, FileEntry array\n  - Missing path: HTTP 400\n  - Path escape: HTTP 400\n  - Non-existent directory: HTTP 500\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T10.7** Test `DownloadFileHandler` scenarios\n  - Existing file: HTTP 200, file content\n  - Leading slash stripped: resolved correctly\n  - Path escape: HTTP 400\n  - File not found: HTTP 404\n  - Path is directory: HTTP 400, `\"path is not a file\"`\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T10.8** Test `HealthCheckHandler`\n  - No JWT required: HTTP 200\n  - Response contains status=\"ok\", service=\"PicoD\", version=\"0.0.1\"\n  - Uptime is duration string\n  - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n\n- [ ] **T10.9** Test `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv` scenarios\n  - Missing env var: error\n  - Invalid PEM: error\n  - PKCS#1 format: not supported, error\n  - Valid PKIX PEM: returns RSA public key\n  - Independently verifiable: Tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Phase 11: Validation and Integration\n\n- [ ] **T11.1** Run `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n  - Verify: No warnings\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T11.2** Run `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n  - Verify: No errors\n  - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n\n- [ ] **T11.3** Run all tests with race detector\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n  - Independently verifiable: All tests pass\n\n- [ ] **T11.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n  - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n  - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n  - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n\n- [ ] **T11.5** Run binary with test public key\n  - Generate RSA key pair\n  - Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n  - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n  - Call `/health`: verify 200 response\n  - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All 8 source files created in `pkg/picod/`\n- [ ] Entry point `cmd/picod/main.go` created\n- [ ] Config struct with Port and Workspace fields\n- [ ] Server struct with Gin engine, AuthManager, workspace, startTime\n- [ ] JWT RS256 authentication with 5 error cases\n- [ ] Execute handler with timeout, working_dir, env support\n- [ ] File upload handler supporting multipart and JSON/Base64\n- [ ] File list and download handlers with path sanitization\n- [ ] Health check handler (no auth required)\n- [ ] sanitizePath with workspace jail enforcement\n- [ ] Pass `go vet`\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n- [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n- [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and executes commands\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines Changed |\n|------|--------|---------------|\n| `go.mod` | Modify | +2 (gin, jwt dependencies) |\n| `pkg/picod/config.go` | Create | ~15 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/server.go` | Create | ~80 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/auth.go` | Create | ~100 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/execute.go` | Create | ~100 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/files.go` | Create | ~150 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/health.go` | Create | ~20 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` | Create | ~50 lines |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Create | ~40 lines |\n| `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Create | ~200 lines |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Gin framework: `gin.New()` for engine, `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` for production\n- JWT validation: use `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n- RSA signing: type-assert `token.Method` to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n- Path sanitization: `filepath.EvalSymlinks()` for symlink resolution, `filepath.Rel()` for traversal check\n- Command execution: `exec.CommandContext()` for timeout enforcement, exit code 124 for timeout\n- Base64 decoding: `base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString()` for JSON file upload\n- File mode parsing: `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` for octal parsing"},"outp